BT /F2 20 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 726 Tm (Chunking And Overlap Explanation) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 663 Tm (1. What Chunking Means) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 616 Tm (Chunking means splitting a long document into smaller pieces before creating embeddings.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 578 Tm (Instead of embedding one full PDF page or one full long article, the code breaks the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 563 Tm (text into manageable chunks.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 525 Tm (This is important because retrieval works better when each stored unit is focused and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 510 Tm (short enough to represent one idea clearly.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 466 Tm (2. Why Chunking Is Needed) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 419 Tm (If a very large document is embedded as one single vector:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 381 Tm (- many topics get mixed together) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 364 Tm (- retrieval becomes less precise) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 347 Tm (- the returned context may include too much irrelevant information) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 309 Tm (Chunking improves:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 271 Tm (- retrieval precision) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 254 Tm (- prompt size control) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 237 Tm (- evidence quality) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 193 Tm (3. Your Project Settings) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 146 Tm (In `rag_chromadb_demo.py`, the code uses:) Tj ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 110 Tm (CHUNK_SIZE = 1000) Tj ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 96 Tm (CHUNK_OVERLAP = 150) Tj ET
endstream
