BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 736 Tm (Meaning:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 698 Tm (- each chunk is about 1000 characters long) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 681 Tm (- each chunk overlaps the next one by about 150 characters) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 637 Tm (4. How Chunking Works Step By Step) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 590 Tm (The function `chunk_text_for_rag\(\)` does this:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 552 Tm (1. cleans whitespace) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 535 Tm (2. starts at position `0`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 518 Tm (3. takes up to `chunk_size` characters) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 501 Tm (4. tries to stop at a space instead of cutting in the middle of a word) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 484 Tm (5. stores that chunk) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 467 Tm (6. moves forward, but backs up by `chunk_overlap`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 450 Tm (7. repeats until the text is finished) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 406 Tm (5. Example Without Overlap) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 359 Tm (Suppose the text is:) Tj ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 323 Tm (Safe weight loss requires a calorie deficit, balanced nutrition, and regular physical activity over time.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 286 Tm (If chunks are split with no overlap:) Tj ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 250 Tm (Chunk 1: Safe weight loss requires a calorie deficit,) Tj ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 236 Tm (Chunk 2: balanced nutrition, and regular physical activity over time.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 199 Tm (Problem:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 161 Tm (- the idea is split in the middle) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 144 Tm (- one chunk has the start of the thought) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 127 Tm (- the next chunk has the rest) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 83 Tm (6. Example With Overlap) Tj ET
endstream
