BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 265 Tm (So each new chunk repeats the final 150 characters from the previous chunk.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 221 Tm (8. Why Overlap Helps Retrieval) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 174 Tm (Overlap reduces boundary problems.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 136 Tm (Boundary problem means:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 98 Tm (- important information is cut exactly where one chunk ends) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 81 Tm (- the next chunk starts without enough context) Tj ET
