BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 713 Tm (Overlap helps because:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 675 Tm (- related sentences stay partially connected) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 658 Tm (- definitions and warnings are less likely to be split badly) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 641 Tm (- retrieval can still succeed even when the best match is near a chunk edge) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 597 Tm (9. Why Not Make Chunks Very Large) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 550 Tm (Huge chunks cause problems:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 512 Tm (- embeddings become less focused) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 495 Tm (- unrelated topics get mixed together) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 478 Tm (- final prompts become larger and noisier) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 461 Tm (- ranking quality often drops) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 423 Tm (So chunking trades one large noisy vector for many smaller, more meaningful vectors.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 379 Tm (10. Why Not Make Chunks Too Small) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 332 Tm (Very tiny chunks also cause problems:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 294 Tm (- not enough context) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 277 Tm (- definitions may become incomplete) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 260 Tm (- recommendations may lose the sentence that explains the condition or warning) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 222 Tm (So chunk size must balance:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 184 Tm (- focus) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 167 Tm (- context) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 150 Tm (- retrieval quality) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 106 Tm (11. Why 1000 And 150 Are Reasonable Here) Tj ET
endstream
