BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 571 Tm (- PDF-derived content) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 527 Tm (12. How The Code Avoids Ugly Splits) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 480 Tm (Inside `chunk_text_for_rag\(\)`:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 442 Tm (- it does not blindly cut at exactly `start + chunk_size`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 425 Tm (- it looks backward for a space) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 408 Tm (- if it finds a good space, it stops there instead) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 370 Tm (That means chunks usually end at natural word boundaries.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 332 Tm (This makes chunk text cleaner for both retrieval and final prompting.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 288 Tm (13. Where Chunking Is Used In Your Project) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 241 Tm (Chunking is applied in two places:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 203 Tm (- `load_documents_from_text_files\(\)`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 186 Tm (- `load_documents_from_pdf_files\(\)`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 148 Tm (That means both local text documents and PDF page text are split before embedding.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 104 Tm (14. Chunking And RAG Flow) Tj ET
endstream
